Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Brazil. The Brazilian authorities have introduced a number of measures to limit the spread of the virus.
You should comply with any additional screening measures put in place by the authorities.
International travel
At the moment the Brazilian Government has not announced that they will stop international flights, and there are flights, but many airlines are reducing or cancelling their domestic and international services. This situation can change at short notice.
Further information
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
You can find more information about cases in Brazil on the TravelHealthPro website.
